The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 New Delhi, July 5 (PTI): The MRTPC has started a judicial probe against ABN AMRO for allegedly adopting deceptive methods in its credit card business. The bank has been asked to reply to a notice within four weeks. 

 Pune (PTI): A teenager poured hot water on her sleeping aunt and hit her with a wooden stick after being slapped for smashing the remote when she was asked to reduce the TV volume. Kumuda Tripathi, a teacher, is in hospital. Namita has been arrested.

 dore (PTI): A court has dismissed a petition against Shilpa Shetty and Richard Gere over a peck at an AIDS awareness programme, saying it was not vulgar.

 New Delhi (PTI): The Central Information Commission has asked the home ministry to furnish documents relied on by two panels on Subhash Chandra Boses alleged death to an organisation, the Mission Netaji. 




